  1. Celebrate Earth Day!

    Join the City for the annual Earth Day celebration at beautiful Lake Lotus Park. Enjoy animals, exhibits, activities, nature walks and more. Let's celebrate!

  2. Tree Giveaway

    We love trees! The City has been celebrating Arbor Day for nearly 30 years by giving away trees to our residents. Supplies are limited. Don't miss out!

  3. The Bookmobile Is Coming!

    Come check out the OverDrive Digital Bookmobile! Learn all about ebooks and audiobooks on May 5 at Family Fest and May 7 at the City Library. I'll be there!

  4. City News

    The latest issue of the Altamonte Springs newsletter has arrived. Flip through the pages for the latest city information, programs and events. Read on...

  5. Flood Information

    Hurricane season is just around the corner. Before the storms come and the waters rise, learn what steps you need to take to protect your home and property. Get prepared.

    Are you ready to join the team? The City is always looking for talented people willing to dedicate themselves to serving our community. View our open positions.

Welcome to Altamonte Springs!

Altamonte Springs is a city born of innovation, fiscal responsibility and progressive ideas. The City has worked hard over the years to remain debt free while maintaining one of the lowest tax rates in Florida. City leadership, staff, residents and local businesses share a vision of making Altamonte Springs the best place in Central Florida to live, work, raise a family, earn a degree, seek medical care, build a business and more.

From forward-thinking projects and proactive initiatives to an evolving business climate and environmentally-friendly projects, Altamonte Springs has set an example for other municipalities by striving to work beyond the typical constraints of local government. 

The City has a perfect blend of community spirit and bustling activities that help create a wholesome environment for residents and visitors alike. Tree-lined streets and beautiful, natural parks reflect the charming and unique character of what locals call home. Not to mention, their robust events program is the most exciting in the region, all generously funded by the area’s corporate sponsors. Hosting more than one million visitors each year, the City’s programs infuse into our community a sense of excitement and entertainment, while enriching our diverse social fabric.

Visit the Winchester Beer Cheese Festival!

Beer Cheese dates back to the 1940's in Clark Co. when it is believed to first be made by Joe Allman for his cousin, John Allman's, restaurants on the Kentucky River. Since then people have fallen for this delicious spread that goes great on carrots, celery, crackers, or anything you want!

MAYOR'S NOTE

Welcome to the Community of Winchester and Clark County. This portal to our Community is our effort to demonstrate that we are a unique blend of devotion to history and tradition and a progressive attitude that casts a forward glance at a prosperous future.

Communicating with our Citizens and to all Citizens who choose to check us out has been a major objective of ours as we rebuilt our website.

Please spend some time here. If you do so we hope you will be pleased with what we have to share. If not, please contact us and we will address your concerns.

Founded in 1793 on what was then the Western Frontier, The City of Winchester served then as a building block for the County of Clark and the new Commonwealth. Located where the Eastern Appalachians kiss the Bluegrass, we are home to vibrant businesses and industry, a healthy Downtown, and a human spirit excelled by none other. We rest easily in the midst of lush, rolling landscapes and breathtaking rural beauty.

We hope you will not only check us out here but will check us out in person.
